== Image sources ==

Most public domain images are likely to be from US Federal Government sources - especially for modern images.

Resources to be checked and added:
* http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/6-free-websites-public-domain-images-free-stock-photos/

Challenges - problematic galleries that have been added:
* [http://www.burningwell.org/ BurningWell.org] - not well indexed by Google (e.g. search for ''solar'' - many more turn up by using ), and it's almost a certainty that some users will have uploaded copyright images, in spite of the intention of the site.

Challenges - galleries which have not been added:
* http://www.doedigitalarchive.doe.gov/ very restrictive (have to "order" high res images; not indexed by search engines). [https://twitter.com/appropedia/status/276292536077807617 Asked via @appropedia]: 
"@ENERGY Hi - the images at www.doedigitalarchive.doe.gov are the work of US Federal employees, I presume? I.e. #PublicDomain under US law?"
* https://public.ornl.gov/site/gallery/default.cfm - public domain is implicitly acknowledged in footer, but site appears not to be indexed by Google. (Mostly science research images - some relevant to Appropedia.)
* [https://www.nsf.gov/news/mmg/ US National Science Foundation - Multimedia Gallery] - not indexed by Google, and its own https://www.nsf.gov/news/mmg/mmg_search.cfm seems to be broken, so the nearly 3000 images can only be viewed by [https://www.nsf.gov/news/mmg/index.cfm?s=0 paging through 30 at a time]. Limited range of themes - science more than technology

Note the explanations of public domain on the [[Public Domain Search]]. Not all images on .gov sites are public domain, for example:
* Anything on state, territory or local government sites.
* Any work done under contract ''may'' be under copyright. For example, Los Alamos National Lab's [Photo Galleries] - note that the [http://www.lanl.gov/resources/web-policies/copyright-legal.php Copyright, Legal] notice claims copyright, which may be justified as the Lab's work is performed under contract rather than as direct employment by the federal government.)

Indexes of US Federal Government galleries. Some will be suitable:
* http://www.usa.gov/Topics/Graphics.shtml

